Summary of ASX Announcement:

  • Upcoming Investor Webinar (8 July 2025, 11:00 AEST) – Focus on:
  • Strategic drill program at Minbrie copper-zinc project (SA).

  • Updates on broader project portfolio.

  • Minbrie Project Key Details:

  • Resource Potential: 7km strike, shallow (<300m) open-pit potential.
  • Highlighted Drill Result: 29.5m @ 0.8% Cu, 7.5% Pb, 1.9% Zn, 9.0 g/t Ag.
  • Infrastructure: Proximity to Port Pirie Smelter (~265km), 100% owned by LML.

(No capital raising, financials, or material catalysts disclosed beyond exploratory updates.)

Conclusion: Operational update only; no immediate trading-impacting data.

• FY26 Reinsurance Program Update:
  • Structure: Main catastrophe cover ($500M–$6.3B), structured multi-year solution (replaces Group cover), NZ buydown cover (NZ$200M–$350M).

  • Key Changes:

    • Lower Cost: Total program cost expected to be below FY25 due to rate reductions.
    • Retention: Maximum event retention unchanged at $350M for 1st/2nd events; 3rd/4th event dropdowns remain ($250M/$150M in Australia).
    • New Features: Added 2nd reinstatement for $500M–$1B layer; profit-sharing mechanism in structured cover (reinsurer losses capped at $600M over 3 years).

  • Impact:

  • Earnings: No material change to risk retention or capital targets.
  • Pricing: Reinsurance cost stability may support underlying insurance margin (10–12% target).

  • Capital Management: Excess capital return update to be provided with full-year results (August).

  • Market Context: Reinsurance capacity increased for main catastrophe covers; pricing improved.

Note: Focus on cost reduction, margin stability, and capital return potential. Operational details (e.g., dropdowns) reflect risk management adjustments.

Summary excludes non-material commentary on strategic reviews, brokers, or NZ-specific dropdowns.

Capital Raising Announcement:
- Structure: Renounceable rights issue ($9m) + placement to Amari Metals Australia Pty Ltd ($6m min., up to $15m total).
- Total Raised: Minimum $15m, maximum $24m at $0.03 per share.
- Key Dates: Shareholder meeting expected late August 2025; documentation to be sent early August.
- New Cornerstone Investor: Amari Metals to own 51% post-completion.
- New Loan Facility: 3-year facility agreed (terms aligned with current pricing).
- Conditions: Shareholder approval, final documentation, and cross-completion required.

June Quarter FY 2026 Investor Update - Key Highlights:

  • Combogesic IV® launch in Canada begins this month, targeting non-opioid pain management in a market growing at 6.1% CAGR (forecast to reach US$1.88B by 2030).
  • US Maxigesic licensing agreement extended with Hikma Pharmaceuticals: Restructured profit-sharing (quarterly payments) and expanded marketing rights for Combogesic IV/Rapid.
  • R&D pipeline milestones:
  • Pre-IND filed for antibiotic eyedrop (targeting MRSA-resistant infections); IND targeted by year-end.
  • Pre-IND for Strawberry Birthmarks topical treatment and IND for novel iron injection planned by year-end.
  • Added improved formulation project (US$180M niche market potential).
  • Paediatric Maxigesic IV study to commence, addressing unmet needs in hospital pain management.
  • Global expansion: Further OTC and in-licensed product launches planned in FY26 across Canada, Singapore, Hong Kong, and other markets.

No material financial data (e.g., cash balance) disclosed.
